Dialogue: 5,0:02:15.92,0:02:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:20.39,0:02:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:22.50,0:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:29.03,0:02:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:33.56,0:02:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Shigeru!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:34.70,0:02:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:44.92,0:02:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been taken by the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.57,0:03:07.58,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an9\bord0\blur0.6\p1\c&H4D4C6F&\pos(1282,66)\fscx600\fscy90}m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.57,0:03:07.58,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an6\blur0.6\pos(920,108)}Mud Grass
Dialogue: 5,0:03:14.56,0:03:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to take a look at our warts.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:16.80,0:03:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a mushi-shi, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:18.63,0:03:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a doctor be more helpful?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:22.80,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:26.68,0:03:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When did these begin to appear?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:29.24,0:03:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone started to get them three days ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:34.02,0:03:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They make the legs go numb, \Nand they're very painful.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:36.59,0:03:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's having a hard time.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:40.05,0:03:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone must have gone into the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:42.64,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder we're all infected by death.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:46.13,0:03:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Infected by death"?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:50.90,0:03:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Four days ago, one of our fellow villagers died.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:58.42,0:04:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,According to our customs,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:01.03,0:04:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we must put our dead in one of the swamps in those mountains
Dialogue: 5,0:04:05.07,0:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave them there.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:09.06,0:04:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Within just seven days,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:10.72,0:04:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,even their bones vanish completely, leaving behind only their clothes.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:17.96,0:04:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is our belief that the dead return to the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:24.36,0:04:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For those seven days, however,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:27.89,0:04:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,our customs also dictate \Nthat it is forbidden to enter the mountains{ until the process is complete}.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.64,0:04:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,According to legend,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:35.36,0:04:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a villager long ago {once }violated that rule
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.08,0:04:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and returned from the mountains \Nwith a pestilence that ravaged the entire village.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:44.96,0:04:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're all afraid the same thing has happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.04,0:04:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These must be Mukurosou seedlings.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:58.72,0:05:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a mushi that decomposes corpses \Nand turns them into mud, down to the bones.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.60,0:05:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When a live animal steps on them, it inadvertently spreads them.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:09.72,0:05:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Other animals that step on the spread seedlings become their hosts.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:15.59,0:05:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The villagers' legend matches these details.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:17.89,0:05:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That confirms it.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:31.62,0:05:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Please allow me to try this.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:42.08,0:05:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It fell off!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:43.33,0:05:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The wart just fell right off!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.58,0:05:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the numbness in my legs is gone too!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ah, here they are.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.37,0:06:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now to just sprinkle salt on the "grass" itself...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:14.37,0:06:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:21.25,0:06:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, do you need some medicine as well?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:25.83,0:06:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please take a look at my uncle?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:40.68,0:06:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I pull them out,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:42.49,0:06:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they grow right back.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:44.87,0:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I touched them, they spread to my hands.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:52.58,0:06:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The medicine has no effect.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:55.08,0:06:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is a very different case from the others.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.67,0:07:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the one who went into the mountains?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:06.85,0:07:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:09.54,0:07:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who passed away was my younger brother.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:13.36,0:07:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I took his son, and we went {into the mountains}up there to pay our respects.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:17.03,0:07:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why risk violating custom?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:22.13,0:07:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time, I thought it was just an old wives' tale.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:28.68,0:07:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago, my daughter went missing.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:35.25,0:07:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When we checked the mountains, we only found her clothes.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:39.09,0:07:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone said it was the mountains that took her.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:44.76,0:07:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But the more I thought about it, the more I realized that \Nno one who went into the mountains back then got sick.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:50.82,0:07:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought it would be fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:54.88,0:07:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When you saw your brother's body, \Nwas it in the process of "returning" to the mountains?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:03.38,0:08:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:13.56,0:08:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see Dad.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:16.93,0:08:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving him in the mountains \N all alone like that is just too mean.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:22.61,0:08:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:25.65,0:08:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go say good-bye to him one last time.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:46.66,0:08:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this stupid grass doing on him?!{Generous timing. :)}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:49.76,0:08:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:52.12,0:08:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:08.74,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad really {\i1}has{\i0} become part of the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:18.72,0:09:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This grass is continuing to live on in Dad's stead.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.08,0:09:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now, let's head back.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:45.94,0:09:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all alone now.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:49.04,0:09:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, would you like to come live with me?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:53.46,0:09:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even think of me as your father{, if you'd like}. How's that?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:57.04,0:09:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, let's go home.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:00.82,0:10:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:06.31,0:10:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since that night,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:08.01,0:10:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had this grass growing from my legs,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.92,0:10:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it keeps on growing.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:15.33,0:10:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's strange.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:18.58,0:10:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}According to records, there {\i0}have{\i1} been others who developed \Nsymptoms after {accidentally }stepping on a body that had turned to "mud."
Dialogue: 5,0:10:24.48,0:10:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, all of them were able to be cured by medicine.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.41,0:10:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what's different in this case?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:31.43,0:10:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it because he was related to the deceased?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.87,0:10:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can't be. If that were the cause, \Nthe nephew would have the same condition.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:39.04,0:10:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something else must be afoot.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.33,0:10:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They intentionally went to the body's location
Dialogue: 5,0:10:45.56,0:10:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and stepped on the "mud."
Dialogue: 5,0:10:54.48,0:10:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If it got on them only when they went to pay their respects...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:59.27,0:11:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If I may ask, how did your brother die?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:05.38,0:11:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sousuke, please go outside for a bit.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:13.56,0:11:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell from a cliff.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:16.37,0:11:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have landed badly,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:18.40,0:11:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because by the time I got to him, he was already...
Dialogue: 5,0:11:22.00,0:11:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was always fond of me.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.60,0:11:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very close.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.90,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I took his death hard.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.19,0:11:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my uncle all better now?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.59,0:11:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet. There are still a few things I need to figure out.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:46.13,0:11:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, though? \NDon't you want me to treat you too?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:49.78,0:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:53.76,0:11:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This grass is with me in Dad's place.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:00.23,0:12:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But doesn't it hurt?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.15,0:12:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask me, I doubt your dad \Nwould have wanted to cause you pain.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:10.02,0:12:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I guess you need more time to think about it, \Nso I'll just leave the medicine with your uncle.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.66,0:12:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it when you're ready.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.66,0:12:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what sort of relationship did your dad and {your }uncle have with each other?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:30.29,0:12:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad loved my uncle.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:35.32,0:12:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little, he used to tell me lots of stories about their adventures together.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:41.43,0:12:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the last few years,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:43.97,0:12:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad didn't mention him at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:12.69,0:13:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.64,0:13:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:20.08,0:13:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shinobu?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:21.58,0:13:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so serious.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:24.96,0:13:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you can tell me anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:45.78,0:13:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:48.88,0:13:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.68,0:13:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri's death...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.31,0:14:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all my fault.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:04.83,0:14:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know she was there...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:09.57,0:14:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I crushed her under the cart.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:14.42,0:14:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.56,0:14:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't bear to tell you...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:22.37,0:14:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I took her to the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:27.40,0:14:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:31.35,0:14:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:33.27,0:14:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:39.52,0:14:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have a son of my own.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.48,0:14:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I look at him, what I did haunts me.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:52.34,0:14:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I could do such a thing—
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.64,0:15:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(80,120)}Brother...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:54.92,0:15:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(160,120)}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.00,0:16:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(120,80)}I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:05.51,0:16:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:08.26,0:16:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it already.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:11.06,0:16:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dead!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:24.72,0:16:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or are you still alive after all?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.71,0:16:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Sousuke...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:46.58,0:16:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, I did something truly unforgivable to someone.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:57.64,0:17:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if something should ever happen to me,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:01.65,0:17:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,please don't hate anyone for it.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:06.72,0:17:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look so sad.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:09.06,0:17:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that all of us return \Nto the mountains someday, don't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:16.04,0:17:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's nothing for you to worry about.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:33.84,0:17:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,After some thought, I came up with a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:38.15,0:17:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I'd like you to hear it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:42.84,0:17:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing on your legs is a Mukurosou, or "Corpse Grass" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:47.60,0:17:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Although its most common form resembles mud,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:49.90,0:17:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it reacts to the scent of death from a dead body, \Nand it sprouts like a plant.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:55.01,0:17:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who step on its seedlings become its hosts.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:57.55,0:18:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It may try to sprout from the living, \Nbut it never grows past those "warts."
Dialogue: 5,0:18:02.39,0:18:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In your case, however,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:03.77,0:18:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it is reacting as though you are dead.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:09.03,0:18:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One possible explanation is \Nthat the scent of death is clinging to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:17.89,0:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what are you insinuating?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:23.12,0:18:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of pursuing \Nthis line of inquiry.{Although the CPS here is high, I really like this phrasing.}{i think the line break makes it a little easier to read in the time}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:27.24,0:18:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I am right,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.16,0:18:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if you somehow cleanse yourself so that no scent of death remains on your body,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:34.46,0:18:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the medicine should work.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:38.82,0:18:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If what I've said is relevant at all, you should try it.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.92,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That is all I have to say.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:18.77,0:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you kill Dad?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:23.73,0:19:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you get a crazy idea like that?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:27.43,0:19:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:29.06,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I overheard your conversation with the mushi-shi just now.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.16,0:19:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you tell anyone else about what you heard?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:41.12,0:19:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:46.32,0:19:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:52.47,0:19:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad told me not to hate anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.82,0:20:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've been really good to me, Uncle!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:01.92,0:20:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.69,0:20:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What made you do such a terrible thing?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.95,0:20:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I simply couldn't control my rage.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:17.97,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if I had managed to control it that day,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:23.43,0:20:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it would've ended the same way eventually.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:28.66,0:20:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you'll kill me one day too...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:41.97,0:20:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My legs!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:43.64,0:20:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sousuke—
Dialogue: 5,0:20:46.42,0:20:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry—
Dialogue: 5,0:20:48.16,0:20:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Help—{how do you drown there wtf}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:16.36,0:21:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:16.99,0:21:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck did I just step in?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:20.68,0:21:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You should watch where you step.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.67,0:21:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end,
Dialogue: 5,0:21:35.82,0:21:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't make it back to the mountains...{rip sousuke}
